@node Main "Try_Angle - Documentation"

                             Try_Angle  1.13

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Try_Angle', a @{" Workbench game " link play}, is played on a triangular-shaped
board, where the idea is to move from the top triangle to an 'exit'
triangle located on the lowest row (a triangle marked by a small
'embossed' triangle). As you leave a triangle it will disappear, or
if there is a number greater than 1, the number will decrease by 1
unit, so you can move that number of times on the triangle.

  Some triangles have coloured numbers, so you must go on these
triangles the indicated number of times before they disappear. If
you get to the exit triangle without clearing all the triangles
with coloured numbers, the game is over.

  Have fun!

