@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Try_Angle' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that you need to
have a 4 (or more) colour Workbench.

                             How to play?

  To play, move the 'tripod' icon from the highest triangle to an
'exit' triangle indicated by a small embossed triangle, located on
the lowest row. To move, just click on one of the surrounding
triangles, you can only move from one triangle to the next by one
of its three sides.

  When you leave a triangle, unless it has a number on it, that
triangle will disappear, so be careful not to trap yourself on an
isolated triangle, which would end the game.

  Some triangles have numbers on them, that means that you can go
on it that number of times before it will disappear (i.e.: if
there's a '5' on a triangle, you can go five times on it). Each
time you leave a numbered triangle, that number will decrease by
one.

  When there are triangles that have @{b}coloured@{ub} numbers, it
means that you must go that number of times on those triangles
before going to an exit triangle in order to finish that level of
the game.

  The score is updated by one point every time you leave a triangle,
so the more triangles you move on, the higher the score you will
get!

  If you clear all the triangles, you will get a bonus score, that
is: the double of the points you have made on this level of the
game...

  Have fun!

